<div id="review_1453041941" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1453041941" />
    <a title="Diane Barnes" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7262060-diane-barnes"><img alt="Diane Barnes" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1329773692p2/7262060.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1453041941?book_show_action=true">May 23, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Diane Barnes" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Diane Barnes" href="/user/show/7262060-diane-barnes">Diane Barnes</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7262060-diane-barnes?shelf=bedtime-books">bedtime-books</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1453041941" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3176826247507884491">I have no idea how to review this one, except to say that Yourcenar obviously channeled Hadrian while she was writing this. It feels like a memoir by the man himself. My edition contained an afterward by the author explaining the 25 year on and off again process of writing which was nearly as good as the novel itself. This might have been 5 stars if my knowledge of ancient Greek and Roman history were greater.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


